trans-unit.source: Represents the <see langword="<CipherData>" /> element in XML encryption.
trans-unit.target: Representa o elemento <see langword="<CipherData>" /> na criptografia XML.

trans-unit.source: This class cannot be inherited.
trans-unit.target: Essa classe não pode ser herdada.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.CipherData> class represents the `<CipherData>` element in XML encryption.
trans-unit.target: O <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.CipherData> classe representa o `<CipherData>` elemento na criptografia de XML.

trans-unit.source: It is a required element that provides the encrypted data.
trans-unit.target: É um elemento necessário que fornece os dados criptografados.

trans-unit.source: It must either contain the encrypted data as base64-encoded text of the `<CipherValue>` element, or provide a reference to an external location containing the encrypted data using the `<CipherReference>` element.
trans-unit.target: Ele deve conter os dados criptografados como texto codificado na base64 o `<CipherValue>` elemento, ou forneça uma referência a um local externo que contém os dados criptografados usando o `<CipherReference>` elemento.

trans-unit.source: In many cases, you do not need to directly create a new instance of the <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.CipherData> class.
trans-unit.target: Em muitos casos, você não precisa criar diretamente de uma nova instância do <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.CipherData> classe.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.SignedXml.EncryptedXml%2A>, <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.EncryptedData>, and <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.EncryptedKey> classes create instances for you.
trans-unit.target: O <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.SignedXml.EncryptedXml%2A>, <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.EncryptedData>, e <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.EncryptedKey> classes criam instâncias para você.

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.CipherData> object can have either a <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.CipherReference> property or a <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.CipherData.CipherValue%2A> property, but not both.
trans-unit.target: Um <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.CipherData> objeto pode ter um <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.CipherReference> propriedade ou um <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.CipherData.CipherValue%2A> propriedade, mas não ambos.

trans-unit.source: A <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.CryptographicException> is thrown if both are assigned to a <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.CipherData> object.
trans-unit.target: Um <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.CryptographicException> é gerada se ambos forem atribuídas a um <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.CipherData> objeto.
